{
    "word": "Farthingale",
    "definitions": [
        "A hoop skirt or hoop petticoat, or other light, elastic material, used to extend the petticoat."
    ],
    "examples": [
        "We'll revel it as bravely as the best, . . . With ruffs and cuffs, and farthingales and things."
    ],
    "etymology": "[OE. vardingale, fardingale, fr. OF. vertugale, verdugade, F. vertugade, vertugadin, from Sp. verdugado, being named from its hoops, fr. verdugo a young shoot of tree, fr. verde green, fr. L. viridis. See Verdant.]"
}